Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
deleteRow(25.10)                                              deleteRow(25.10)

Name
       deleteRow - Deletes the specified row(s)

Syntax
        deleteRow

       [-help]

       {-all | -selected | -site <string>| <row>}

       Deletes  the  specified  row(s). Use this command after importing a de-
       sign.

Parameters
       -all   Specifies that all rows will be deleted.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for  each  deleteRow  parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man deleteRow

       <row>  Specifies the name or id of the row(s) to be deleted.

              Data_type: list, required

       -selected
              Specifies that the selected rows should be deleted.

              Data_type: bool, required

       -site <string>
              Specifies the site for which rows will be deleted.

              Data_type: string, required

Example
       The following command deletes rows for the site site0A10.

       deleteRow -site site0A10

